# OpenAI Configuration for BrutusAI
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to ".env" (without quotes)
# 2. Replace 'your_openai_api_key_here' with your actual OpenAI API key
# 3. Your API key should start with 'sk-'
# 4. Restart the development server after adding your key
# 5. Never commit the .env file with a real API key to version control

# Example:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-1234567890abcdef...

# To use this template:
# 1. Copy this file: cp env.template .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual API key
# 3. Restart: npm run web

# Security Note:
# The .env file should be added to .gitignore to prevent accidentally
# committing your API key to the repository 